'''企業戰'''(Corporate warfare)是指企業與企業之間的互相攻擊，其層次可能從利用[[駭客|駭客]]獲取敵對企業的[[商業機密|商業機密]]到甚至引發企業之間的武裝衝突。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Kutais|first1=B. G.|title=Internet Policies and Issues|publisher=Nova Publishers|isbn=9781590332269|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iMZPaZz-JNkC&pg=PA90|accessdate=23 January 2017|language=en|year=1999|archive-date=2021-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211016005021/https://books.google.com/books?id=iMZPaZz-JNkC&pg=PA90|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=targeted1/>此類戰爭可能是[[經濟戰|經濟戰]]和[[網路戰|網路戰]]的一部分。

==科幻小說==
在[[賽博朋克|賽博朋克]]類型的科幻小說中，企業會保護自己的數據並僱員闖入競爭對手的電腦系統。<ref>{{cite web|title=The Politics of Cyberpunk|url=http://project.cyberpunk.ru/idb/politics_of_cyberpunk.html|publisher=The Cyberpunk Project|accessdate=23 January 2017|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111215433/http://project.cyberpunk.ru/idb/politics_of_cyberpunk.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>在[[威廉·吉布森|威廉·吉布森]]（William Gibson）所著的作品中，[[國家|國家]]的權力主要掌握在[[超大型企業|超大型企業]]的手中，這些超大型企業通常擁有自己的安全部隊甚至是私人[[軍隊|軍隊]]，並相互進行企業戰。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Meehan|first1=Paul|title=Tech-Noir: The Fusion of Science Fiction and Film Noir|publisher=McFarland|isbn=9781476609737|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RBFeCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA16|accessdate=23 January 2017|language=en|date=13 August 2015|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021000534/https://books.google.com/books?id=RBFeCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA16|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==網路==
Schwartau認為，在公司[[資訊戰|資訊戰]]中，[[公司|公司]]通常容易成為競爭對手的目標。這種戰爭可能的方法包括從事[[商業間諜|商業間諜]]活動、散佈[[假消息|假消息]]、洩露[[機密|機密]]訊息並損害公司[[資訊系統|資訊系統]]。<ref name=fut1>{{cite journal 
|last1=Merrick |first1=Kathryn |last2=Hardhienata |first2=Medria |last3=Shafi |first3=Kamran |last4=Hu |first4=Jiankun |title=A Survey of Game Theoretic Approaches to Modelling Decision-Making in Information Warfare Scenarios |journal=Future Internet |date=22 July 2016|volume=8|issue=3|pages=34|doi=10.3390/fi8030034|doi-access=free }}</ref>

網絡安全及網絡武器公司Endgame, Inc.的克里斯·魯蘭德（Chris Rouland）極力主張，應允許私人公司對試圖[[竊取數據|竊取數據]]的國家或罪犯進行“駭客反擊”。<ref>{{cite news|title=This Silicon Valley venture fund keeps betting millions on D.C.'s cyber community|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/capitalbusiness/this-silicon-valley-venture-fund-keeps-betting-millions-on-dcs-cyber-community/2016/08/19/9cc68634-658f-11e6-96c0-37533479f3f5_story.html|newspaper=Washington Post|access-date=23 January 2017|archive-date=2020-10-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201007110433/https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/capitalbusiness/this-silicon-valley-venture-fund-keeps-betting-millions-on-dcs-cyber-community/2016/08/19/9cc68634-658f-11e6-96c0-37533479f3f5_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

